               <h2 class="dark">Men's ministries</h2>
               <dl class="list4">
                  <dd>
                     <p>For the men of the Body of Jesus Christ to be intimately and thoroughly in<br>
                      love with Him, and to show His Love for everyone in our relationship with the<br>
                      entire Body of Christ, our own family's at home, and the world. To study His<br>
                      Holy Bible praying for guidance from the Holy Spirit, and last but not least<br>
                      Matthew 7:24-27. To hear and do His Will, standing on that solid Rock, Jesus<br>
                     Christ.</p>
                  </dd>
               </dl>
               <h2 class="dark">JPCF Youth Ministry Vision</h2>
               <p class="extra2">Ministering to our Youth, through songs, dance, drama, Christian games, crafts and visuals aids to include demonstrating the character of Christ through our teachers. JPCF's Youth Ministry endeavor's to train children in the Word of God, teaching them the scriptures, how to pray, worship, evangelize, and serve so that they will develop a strong Christian foundation built upon Jesus Christ.  JPCF helps our Youth develop an intimate relationship with Jesus Christ; by applying the Word of God to every aspect of their lives.  Being sensitive to the Holy Spirit, JPCF will nurture their love for God and each other, by making the Holy Scriptures the cornerstone of their Christian training.</p>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="box third maxheight">
            <div class="inner1">
               <h2 class="dark">women's  ministries</h2>
               <p>Women's Ministry Vision Verse</p>
               <p>"A NEW COMMAND I FOR YOU, 
               THAT YOU LOVE ONE ANOTHER; EVEN AS I<br>
               HAVE LOVED YOU, YOU MUST LOVE ONE ANOTHER, BY THIS THE WORLD<br>
               WILL KNOW THAT YOU ARE MY DISCIPLES, IF YOU LOVE ONE ANOTHER."</p>
               <p>Our Mission is three fold:</p>
               <p><b>To build intentional relationships by:</b><br>
               * Widening our circle of friendships among women within the church family<br>
               * Spending purposeful time with women outside the family of God.</p>
               <p><b>To strengthen women by:</b><br>
               * Spending time in the Word of God.<br>
               * Entering the Word of God in our conversations when we are together.<br>
               * Prioritizing time for worship and prayer.<br>
               * Encouraging women to participate in all matters relating to the woman's heart.<br>
               * Encouraging women to be a part of the women's Bible study.</p>
               <p><b>Serving God by using our giftedness for the benefit of others by:</b><br>
               * Adjusting our time to express care and meet needs of others.<br>
               * Becoming equipped in the skills needed for ministry within the body of Christ.<br>
               * Becoming equipped in the skills needed to reach the lost by multiplying leaders through<br>
               a coaching/mentoring process.</p>
               <p class="extra">&nbsp;</p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="box third maxheight">
         <div class="inner1">
            <h2 class="dark">Vision In Action (VIA)</h2>
              <p><span style="font-size:14px;">VIA Ministries is ordained as a World Outreach Ministry that welcomes people in whatever condition they find themselves to be in. Our goal is to fulfill the needs of all God's children by providing clothing, food, shelter and love. Following after Christ example we reach out to all who are in need through the love of Christ. Our passion is to   go to the highways and byways; to the hospitals, homes and to the streets, to   those who are imprisoned by cell bars or the prison bars of those who are held captive by the condition of their spirit and soul. Our hearts and hands are open to, men, women and children regardless of their position in the community, financial status, age or circumstances.   
              </span>
              <p><span style="font-size:14px;">VIA supports other mission projects at the local, state, national and international levels. Submitting ourselves to the leading of the Holy Spirit, who will teach and guide us into all truth. Through our prayers, financial   offerings, and self-sacrifice, we are committed to ministering and building of souls for the Kingdom of God, in Christ Jesus.   
              </span>
              <p style="font-size:14px;">"...for I was hungry and you gave Me food; I was thirsty and you gave Me drink;   I was a stranger and you took Me in; I was naked and you clothed Me; I was sick   and you visited Me; I was in prison and you came to Me..." Matthew 25:35-36 NKJ </p>
        
         </div>
      </div>
